                            <comment id="15313042" author="garydgregory" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 20:57:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In Git master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313123" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 21:39:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is misleading about the warning message?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313178" author="garydgregory" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 22:07:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In my case, there is nothing wrong with the messages being logged. It&apos;s just Log4j that does not know any better. There is also nothing I can do about as a user.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313186" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 22:13:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So what was the fix?  Saying &quot;In Git master&quot; doesn&apos;t tell me what was done about the reported problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313194" author="garydgregory" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 22:19:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the description for this issue to show the root of the problem and the remedy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313253" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 23:05:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See also discussion at the bottom of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1180&quot; title=&quot;Logger cache does not account for message factory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-1180&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-1180&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. We were wrapping the factory in a MessageFactory2Adapter (even the default factory), and comparing the wrapper to the default factory. No match, hence warning. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
